<nav class="nav" id="nav" data-screen-label="Nav"><svg class="sunmark" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"><circle class="sun-disc" cx="16" cy="16" r="10"></circle></svg><a class="wm" href="/">AMPM <small>BUILDING SERVICES</small></a><div class="links"><a href="/services/" class="">Services</a><a href="/work/" class="">Work</a><a href="/compliance/" class="">Compliance</a><a href="/about/" class="">About</a><a href="/contact/" class="">Contact</a></div><a class="phone" href="tel:03300430080">0330 043 0080</a></nav><div class="page" style="--svc: var(--m-purple);"><div class="shell"><section class="sec p-hero"><div class="reveal in"><span class="svc-bar" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span></div><div class="reveal in"><div class="kicker">Services · 02</div></div><h1 class="reveal d1 in">Fit-out &amp; Refurbishment</h1><p class="lede reveal d2 in">Commercial fit-out and refurbishment, with the M&amp;E held in-house rather than sub-let. That single decision removes the most common source of programme slip on a fit-out — and it's why occupiers and Tier-1s hand us <strong>the whole floor, not just the trades.</strong></p><div class="reveal d3 in" style="margin-top: 28px;"><a class="btn line sm" href="/contact/">Enquire about a fit-out →</a></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">What we deliver</div><h2 class="dhead sm">The full Commercial scope,<br>self-delivered.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Category-A</span></h4><ul><li>Raised floors &amp; ceilings</li><li>Base-build M&amp;E coordination</li><li>Shell upgrades</li><li>Landlord Cat-A finish</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Category-B</span></h4><ul><li>Partitioning &amp; dry-lining</li><li>Joinery &amp; finishes</li><li>Tea-points &amp; breakout</li><li>Furniture coordination</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Refurbishment</span></h4><ul><li>Strip-out &amp; reconfiguration</li><li>Occupied / live works</li><li>Landlord re-lets</li><li>Phased programmes</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Integrated M&amp;E</span></h4><ul><li>M&amp;E held in-house</li><li>One programme, one PM</li><li>Move-in dates that hold</li><li>Single snag list</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">How we work</div><h2 class="dhead sm">From survey to handover —<br>one accountable team.</h2></div><ol class="steps reveal in"><li class="step"><span class="step-n">01</span><div><h4>Survey &amp; measure</h4><p>We survey the existing space, take measured surveys and pin down the brief — base-build constraints, landlord requirements and the move-in date that has to hold.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">02</span><div><h4>Design, samples &amp; programme</h4><p>Coordinated design, material samples and a buildable programme — Cat A or Cat B — with long-lead items and FF&amp;E flagged early so nothing stalls the fit-out later.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">03</span><div><h4>Strip-out &amp; enabling</h4><p>Soft strip, enabling works and protection to base build — sequenced around live, occupied floors and out-of-hours where the building has to keep running.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">04</span><div><h4>Partitions, M&amp;E &amp; ceilings</h4><p>Dry-lining, partitions and ceilings installed alongside a fully coordinated M&amp;E package — the same contractor, so the services and the fabric never fall between two trades.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">05</span><div><h4>Finishes, joinery, FF&amp;E &amp; handover</h4><p>Bespoke joinery, finishes and FF&amp;E to a Cat B standard, then a managed snag, demonstration and clean handover with full O&amp;M and as-built records.</p></div></li></ol></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Standards &amp; compliance</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Built to the codes that<br>matter on handover.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>The standards we build to</span></h4><ul><li>CDM 2015 across every package</li><li>Building Regulations Part B — fire safety</li><li>Building Regulations Part M — access, Part K &amp; Part E — acoustics</li><li>BS 8000 — workmanship on building sites</li><li>BS 9999 &amp; BS 9991 — fire safety in design</li><li>BCO Guide to Specification</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Backed by AMPM Group</span></h4><ul><li>The Group’s accreditations behind every job</li><li>29 years of group trading history, since 1997</li><li>One project manager accountable per programme</li><li>Phased delivery around occupied, live buildings</li><li>PQQ and reference packs on request</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">Sectors</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Where fit-out<br>lands best.</h2></div><div class="sectorrow reveal in"><span class="sector">Commercial offices</span><span class="sector">Workplace</span><span class="sector">Hospitality &amp; leisure</span><span class="sector">Retail</span><span class="sector">Healthcare</span><span class="sector">Education</span><span class="sector">Labs &amp; R&amp;D</span><span class="sector">Public sector</span></div><p class="body" style="margin-top:22px;max-width:60ch;">We deliver fit-out across London and the South East — including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire — for direct clients, Tier-1 main contractors and blue-chip FM providers.</p></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="intro2 reveal in"><div><div class="kicker">Market drivers</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Where the work<br>is coming from.</h2></div><p class="body">Office refurbishment, landlord re-lets and Cat-A / Cat-B fit-out for Tier-1 main contractors and direct occupiers.</p></div></section><section class="sec"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Representative projects</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Commercial work, in the field.</h2></div><div class="caselist reveal in"><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1604328698692-f76ea9498e76?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — Commercial" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-purple); position: absolute;">Commercial · Cat-A/B</span><h4>Landlord re-let — London</h4><p class="cs">Cat-A upgrade followed by Cat-B fit for the incoming tenant.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£1.6m</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">20 wks</div></div></div></div><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1524758631624-e2822e304c36?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — Commercial" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-purple); position: absolute;">Commercial · Refurb</span><h4>Occupied HQ — Kent</h4><p class="cs">Phased refurbishment delivered in a live, occupied environment.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£2.1m</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">28 wks</div></div></div></div><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1577412647305-991150c7d163?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — Commercial" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-purple); position: absolute;">Commercial · Fit-out</span><h4>Office — South East</h4><p class="cs">Joinery, partitioning and finishes to a full commercial floor.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£680k</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">14 wks</div></div></div></div></div><p class="case-note">Representative of the Commercial work we are set up to deliver. Named, full-format case studies follow as projects complete — PQQ references available on request.</p></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">FAQs</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Fit-out questions,<br>answered.</h2></div><div class="faq reveal in"><details class="faq-item"><summary>What’s the difference between Cat A and Cat B fit-out?</summary><p>Cat A is the landlord’s base finish — raised floors, suspended ceilings, basic M&amp;E and a blank, lettable shell. Cat B is the occupier fit-out on top: partitions, joinery, finishes, branding, meeting rooms and FF&amp;E. We deliver both, and the transition between them.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can you work in an occupied or live building, in phases?</summary><p>Yes. Much of our fit-out work is phased around live, occupied buildings — soft strip and enabling out-of-hours, floor-by-floor sequencing and tight protection to base build — so the building keeps running while we fit it out.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you handle the M&amp;E too?</summary><p>Yes — and it’s the same contractor. We self-deliver the full MEPH package alongside the fabric, so the services and the fit-out are coordinated under one accountable team rather than split across two trades.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>How do you hold the programme and the move-in date?</summary><p>We pin long-lead items and FF&amp;E at design stage, procure early and run a buildable programme with one project manager accountable for it. The move-in date is the fixed point we plan back from.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you cover fire-stopping and compartmentation?</summary><p>Yes. Fire-stopping and compartmentation are built into the package — installed and recorded to support compliance with Building Regulations Part B and the fire-safety design under BS 9999 and BS 9991.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Which areas do you cover?</summary><p>We deliver commercial fit-out across London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire. Send us the site address and we’ll arrange a survey.</p></details></div></section><section class="sec tight line-top"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><div class="kicker">The other three lines</div><h2 class="dhead sm">One contractor,<br>four service lines.</h2></div><div class="otherlines reveal in"><div class="otherline"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span class="ol-nm">MEPH</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></div><div class="otherline"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Fabric</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></div><div class="otherline"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-blue);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Groundworks</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></div></div></section></div><section class="band" data-nav-dark="true" style="background: var(--m-purple); color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div class="shell"><div class="cta-split reveal in"><div><div class="kicker on-dark">Talk to us about Commercial</div><h2 class="dhead sm" style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Scope, programme,<br>stage — send it over.</h2><p class="body" style="color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); margin-top: 16px;">A named contact, not a sales team, comes back within 24 hours. Include the package, programme and stage if you can.</p></div><div class="cta-row2" style="flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;"><a class="btn ghost" href="/contact/">Enquire about a fit-out →</a><a class="btn ghost" href="/compliance/">Compliance &amp; BSA</a></div></div></div></section></div><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What’s the difference between Cat A and Cat B fit-out?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Cat A is the landlord’s base finish — raised floors, suspended ceilings, basic M&E and a blank, lettable shell. Cat B is the occupier fit-out on top: partitions, joinery, finishes, branding and FF&E. AMPM Building Services delivers both."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you work in an occupied or live building, in phases?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Much of our fit-out work is phased around live, occupied buildings — out-of-hours strip-out, floor-by-floor sequencing and tight protection to base build — so the building keeps running while we fit it out."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you handle the M&E too?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, and it is the same contractor. We self-deliver the full MEPH package alongside the fabric, so the services and the fit-out are coordinated under one accountable team."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you hold the programme and the move-in date?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We pin long-lead items and FF&E at design stage, procure early and run a buildable programme with one project manager accountable for it. The move-in date is the fixed point we plan back from."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you cover fire-stopping and compartmentation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Fire-stopping and compartmentation are built into the package — installed and recorded to support compliance